Having just completed installing a new water main at a retired firefighters home in Las Vegas, I was hungry for a good meal and logged into Wi-Fi at Pizza 9 (Great Chicago style pizza! Especially the deep dish, crusty Hawaiian is just Excellent).
 While reflecting on a good job well done to stop wasting water and money $350, 2,500-3,000 GALLONS of WATER/month.. . I decided to post it up to mark the date(:))).. . I'm a 4th generation MasterPlumber and proud to be of service, especially saving water. Alright, just in time, here's my pizza. "Thank you, Ralph. I'll write about it. I just love the food and hospitality here. Friendly, clean, relaxing and good. Great all the way around. Thanks, for being here.
